  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-10-15",
    "date": "2022-02-09T17:54:18Z",
    "text": "Count the Crimes to Cut Act of 2021\n\nThis bill establishes public databases of federal criminal offenses.\n\nSpecifically, the bill requires the Department of Justice to report on and create a public database of all criminal statutory offenses. Additionally, the bill requires federal agencies to report on and create public databases of criminal regulatory offenses that they enforce."
